			<p><b>USS Independence Operational Timeline</b></p><table border='0' cellspacing='0'><tr bgcolor='eeeeee'><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/01/14/1943' alt='See all events on 14 Jan 1943' title='See all events on 14 Jan 1943' class='noStyle'>14 Jan 1943</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Independence was commissioned into service.</td></tr><tr bgcolor=''><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/11/05/1943' alt='See all events on 5 Nov 1943' title='See all events on 5 Nov 1943' class='noStyle'>5 Nov 1943</a>&nbsp;</td><td>USS Independence arrived at Espiritu Santo, New Hebrides.</td></tr><tr bgcolor='eeeeee'><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/08/28/1946' alt='See all events on 28 Aug 1946' title='See all events on 28 Aug 1946' class='noStyle'>28 Aug 1946</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Independence was decommissioned from service.</td></tr><tr bgcolor=''><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/01/26/1951' alt='See all events on 26 Jan 1951' title='See all events on 26 Jan 1951' class='noStyle'>26 Jan 1951</a>&nbsp;</td><td>USS Independence was scuttled about 30 miles (about 50 kilometers) off Half Moon Bay, California, United States.  The wreck would be discovered by the US National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) in 2015.</td></tr></table><br /><p><b>Photographs</b></p><table cellpadding='2' cellspacing='0' border='0'><tr><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=220'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_independence2.jpg" border='0' alt='Independence soon after completion, circa early 1943'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=220'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_55b6a977c407d.jpg" border='0' alt='Light Carrier USS Independence in port, 1943'></a></td><td><a href='/photo.php?source=all&color=all&list=search&foreigntype=S&foreigntype_id=220'><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_indepen